Here is one example of a Java Class that can retrieve the current time in hours, minutes and seconds for the state of California. This implementation requests "America/Los_Angeles" time, although "PST" would also serve the same purpose.

import java.util.*;

public class CaliforniaTime {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Calendar calCali = Calendar.getInstance();
        calCali.setTimeZone(TimeZone.getTimeZone("America/Los_Angeles"));

        int hour = calCali.get(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY);
        int minute = calCali.get(Calendar.MINUTE);
